"on tap at the kitchen in boulder, some sort of double ellies brown ale recipe, but this is next level stuff from avery. deep soilesque brown in color, rich and solid to light, frothy in head, tan, but well carbonated. looks gorgeous. the nose is a sweeter side of the dark malt, less roast, more marshmallow and molasses, a nice twist. sturdy beer, must have been a big mash. i pick up an almost corn sweetness too it, amongst all the earthy malt. shockingly dry though, really highly fermented, minimal residual sugar for the sweet nose. beautifully full body, rich enough for something like a rare lamb burger, but not zoo dominating that a bowl of creamed spinach soup cannot be appreciated. it takes a lot to find that feel in a strong dark beer. this shows no booze at all, and may be the crowning beer in this anniversary series, which has been nothing short of stunning on the whole. perfect food beer, burnt sugars in it make it a dessert in its own right, but something special about the feel. bitter enough, gorgeous."
