"O-This beer is a little odd, but I mostly enjoyed it. If you are expecting a nutty, chocolatey brown, you're in for a surprise because this thing is a hop bomb. That being said, the sweetness from the malts provides an interesting balance to the hops. An interesting mix of styles, but like a lot of hybrid beers, this one is fun for a while, but not a world-beater."
"O - Although I would not buy this again, it was a pleasant experience. This beer gives you the best of two worlds; the hoppiness that I've come to know from Avery and a malty, brown ale that I rarely drink. Well worth trying if you come across it or like this sort of thing."
